"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"One of the Three NIST Post-quantum Signature Finalists\\n\\n**Rainbow belongs to the family of the [multivariate public key cryptosystems](https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FMultivariate_cryptography&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNEu6Hwy-LtMWmcNzu0kOClrEXssIQ), one of the main families of post-quantum cryptosystems. [Rainbow](https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F11496137_12&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNHhyBhHjm747Uz6BM0EUUZ5WZ4ofQ) was designed in 2004 by Jintai Ding and Dieter Schmidt and it is based on the Oil-Vinegar signature scheme invented by Jacques Patarin. In July 22. 2020, Rainbow was select as one of the [three NIST Post-quantum signature finalists](https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fcsrc.nist.gov%2FNews%2F2020%2Fpqc-third-round-candidate-announcement&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNHfsdINteTC1VMqjFaXk7BXYy9Lsw).**\\n\\n**The theoretical security of Rainbow is based on the fact that solving a set of random multivariate quadratic system is an NP-hard problem. The mathematical theory behind is the theory of multivariate polynomials -- algebraic geometry.**\\n\\n**Rainbow offers very small signatures of only a few hundred bits (only 528 bits=66 bytes for the NIST level I security), which are much shorter than those of other (post-quantum) signature schemes. Furthermore, since Rainbow uses only simple operations over small finite fields, signature generation and verification are extremely efficient.**\\n\\n**There are [a short](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tdy1ztYedrA) and [a long](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FrM6zAuI7-4) videos about MPKCs and Rainbow you can watch. [The NIST second round presentation](https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fcsrc.nist.gov%2FCSRC%2Fmedia%2FPresentations%2Frainbow-round-2-presentation%2Fimages-media%2Frainbow-ding.pdf&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNFsCPMRuBZbCi93Xl57SK_T9QP9cw) is also a good place to learn the basics about Rainbow.**\",\"timestamp\":1640842522,\"title\":\"Rainbow Signature\"},\"digest\":\"N4nzU_R5Kt1J2-redAZsOx7lzcMVwQ9mMhnjF7JtQy4\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xF4Ccc614FfCAC96490B3B56b382108C3C2f4F645\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"1f8_fCn5xq1YzSzsY120gmyL2uAS9PD4H-JE_B4JGqc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Oe05sIH06ijz2FfAEWaa3dNgYDSsbPPo0V64Jaz_Bjo\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"i-ZCYd712NRVc5tTPXWcoDxqFOvE0qcj_mTR4JCMM9dR58JqXwez2T6mz0cpZc54BA8kKHTO-wsSJm1UBqvrcQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x01a91e943f70b46e859571fcf7a82be4c68af08d2ee6e3bb017aa1880f1725ef22221b571efccbe0c6f6ff401a72b13b315a1346ac4349c843af5301cd8ae2011c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"1f8_fCn5xq1YzSzsY120gmyL2uAS9PD4H-JE_B4JGqc\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Oe05sIH06ijz2FfAEWaa3dNgYDSsbPPo0V64Jaz_Bjo\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"N4nzU_R5Kt1J2-redAZsOx7lzcMVwQ9mMhnjF7JtQy4\"}"